<div class="container my-5">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-10 offset-md-1">
      <h1 class="text-center mb-4">Your Karma Dashboard</h1>

      <div class="card mb-4 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title">Your Karma Progress</h2>
          <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-2">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Karma Points: <span class="badge bg-success"><%= @user_karma_points %></span></h3>
            <h3 class="mb-0">Rank: <span class="badge bg-info"><%= @user_rank %></span></h3>
          </div>

          <p class="lead">
            Current Tier: <strong><%= @current_karma_tier[:display_name] %></strong>
          </p>

          <% if @next_karma_tier %>
            <p>
              Next Tier: <strong><%= @next_karma_tier[:display_name] %></strong>
              (<%= @next_karma_tier[:min_points] %> Karma Points)
            </p>
            <div class="progress" style="height: 25px;">
              <div class="progress-bar bg-warning" role="progressbar" style="width: <%= @progress_percentage %>%;" aria-valuenow="<%= @progress_percentage %>" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
                <%= @progress_percentage %>%
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-muted text-end mt-1"><small><%= @next_karma_tier[:min_points] - @user_karma_points %> points to go!</small></p>
          <% else %>
            <p class="text-success lead">
              Congratulations! You are a <%= @current_karma_tier[:display_name] %> – you've reached the highest tier!
            </p>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title text-center mb-3">What is Karma?</h2>

          <p class="lead text-center">
            Karma on Map the Makers is our way of celebrating <strong>you</strong>, our amazing community members!
            Every time you contribute to building a richer, more accurate, and helpful resource for conscious consumers in Indonesia,
            you earn Karma points.
          </p>

          <p class="text-center mb-5">
            Think of Karma as your personal impact score – the more you contribute, the more your Karma grows,
            and the more you help others discover incredible local food producers!
          </p>

          <h3 class="mb-3">How to Earn Karma</h3>
          <p>
            Earning Karma is simple! Every action you take to improve Map the Makers helps our community and earns you valuable points:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Add a New Maker:</strong> Help us grow our network! When you successfully add a new farmer,
              butcher, fisherman, or other local producer to Map the Makers, you'll earn Karma points.
              <p class="text-muted mt-1"><em>Karma Points: <%= KarmaConfig::POINTS_FOR_ADDING_MAKER %> points.</em></p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Write a Review:</strong> Share your experiences! Your honest reviews help others make informed decisions.
              <p class="text-muted mt-1"><em>Karma Points: <%= KarmaConfig::POINTS_FOR_SUBMITTING_REVIEW %> points.</em></p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Confirm Data Accuracy (Coming Soon!):</strong> Help us keep our information fresh and reliable.
              If you notice outdated details or can verify existing data, you'll earn Karma.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Participate in Missions (Coming Soon!):</strong> Engage in special challenges and community events.
              These could be anything from adding a certain number of makers in a week to joining local clean-up initiatives.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="mb-3">Karma Tiers: Become a Local Hero!</h3>
          <p>
            As your Karma points grow, you'll unlock special tiers, publicly recognizing your dedication and impact.
            Each tier comes with unique badges displayed on your profile.
          </p>
          <p>Here are the initial tiers:</p>
          <ul>
            <% KarmaConfig::TIERS.each do |key, tier| %>
              <li><strong><%= tier[:display_name] %>:</strong> <%= tier[:min_points] %>+ Karma Points</li>
            <% end %>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted"><em>Note: Karma point thresholds for each tier may be adjusted as the community grows.</em></p>

          <h3 class="mb-3">What Does Karma Do?</h3>
          <p>Beyond the satisfaction of helping your community, Karma offers:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Recognition:</strong> Your Karma points and tier badge will be visible on your profile, showcasing your contributions.</li>
            <li><strong>Influence:</strong> Higher Karma tiers may unlock special privileges in the future, such as early access to new features or the ability to vote on community initiatives.</li>
            <li><strong>Community Connection:</strong> Karma helps highlight the most active and helpful members, fostering a stronger community around local food.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title">Top 10 Karma Leaders</h2>
          <% if @top_users.any? %>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
              <% @top_users.each_with_index do |user, index| %>
                <li class="list-group-item d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                  <div>
                    <strong><%= index + 1 %>. <%= user.email %></strong>
                    <% if user == @user %>
                      <span class="badge bg-primary ms-2">You</span>
                    <% end %>
                  </div>
                  <span class="badge bg-secondary rounded-pill"><%= user.karma_points %> Karma</span>
                </li>
              <% end %>
            </ul>
          <% else %>
            <p class="text-muted">No Karma leaders yet. Be the first to earn points!</p>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
